# Design tokens & visual system

See also: **`interaction-polish.mdc`**, **`src/index.css`**, shadcn skill [`styling.md`](../../skills/shadcn/rules/styling.md), [`customization.md`](../../skills/shadcn/customization.md). Index: [`skills/SKILL.md`](../../skills/SKILL.md).

**All visual styling flows through the theme** — semantic Tailwind classes backed by CSS variables in `src/index.css`. Use **shadcn/ui** as the default UI layer.

## Core rule

**No arbitrary Tailwind values** (`text-[13px]`, `bg-[#1a1a1a]`, `p-[18px]`) and **no hard-coded colors** (hex, `rgb()`, raw palette like `text-gray-600`, inline `style={{ color: … }}`).

Use the **scale** and **semantic tokens** instead.

| Concern | Use | Not |
| ------- | --- | --- |
| **Text size** | `text-xs`, `text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg`, `text-xl` | `text-[13px]` |
| **Spacing** | `gap-2`, `p-4`, `mt-6` | `p-[18px]` |
| **Radius** | `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg`, `rounded-xl` | `rounded-[10px]` |
| **Colors** | `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `text-destructive`, `bg-card` | `#fff`, `bg-zinc-900`, `text-gray-500` |
| **Dark mode** | Semantic tokens (auto via `.dark`) | `bg-white dark:bg-gray-950` |

## shadcn/ui usage

1. **Use installed shadcn components first** — `Button`, `Card`, `Dialog`, `Input`, `Select`, `Tabs`, `Table`, `DropdownMenu`, `Sheet`, `Alert`, `Badge`, `Form`, etc.
2. **Install from shadcn before building custom primitives** when a standard pattern is missing.
3. **Compose product UI from shadcn primitives** — custom `ItemCard` / `RowActionsMenu` still use `@/components/ui/...` for controls.
4. **Avoid** recreating standard controls with raw `<button>`, modal markup, or ad-hoc card styles when shadcn has the primitive.

**Discovery:** read `components.json`; use shadcn Skill/MCP (`pnpm dlx shadcn@latest search`, `add`). Community registries — suggest command, wait for approval before install.

**`className` on primitives** — layout only (`max-w-md`, `flex-1`, `mt-4`). Do not override primitive colors or font sizes the component already encodes.

Interaction completeness (states, keyboard, motion) → **`interaction-polish.mdc`**, **`error-handling.mdc`** — not a second visual theme.

## Semantic colors

| Need | Token / pattern |
| ---- | ---------------- |
| Page surface | `bg-background text-foreground` |
| Card / panel | `bg-card text-card-foreground` |
| Muted copy | `text-muted-foreground` |
| Primary action | `Button` default / `bg-primary text-primary-foreground` |
| Danger | `text-destructive`, `variant="destructive"` |
| Success | `text-success`, `bg-success/10` (after adding `--success` in `index.css`) |
| Warning | `text-warning`, `bg-warning/10` |
| Borders / inputs | `border-border`, `bg-input`, `ring-ring` |

New brand colors → **CSS variable** in `src/index.css` (`:root` / `.dark`) + `@theme inline` — not scattered hex.

## Contrast on tinted surfaces

**Do not** put `text-muted-foreground` on strongly tinted backgrounds without checking contrast — use `text-foreground` or emphasis tokens.

## Theming & dark mode

- **Tokens** — `src/index.css` (`:root`, `.dark`, `@theme inline`)
- **Runtime** — `ThemeProvider` (`next-themes`) toggles `class="dark"` on `<html>`

```tsx
<ThemeProvider attribute="class" defaultTheme="system" enableSystem disableTransitionOnChange>
```

If `.dark` tokens exist, users must be able to choose **light / dark / system** (settings, header menu, or dev-only until user-facing).

### Validation workflow (before merge)

1. Toggle light, dark, and system.
2. Spot-check 2–3 routes (auth, app shell, settings).
3. Grep violations: `slate-`, `gray-`, `bg-white`, `text-[#`, `emerald-`, `amber-`.
4. Check contrast on tinted panels.

### Rebrand

1. Apply shadcn preset or edit CSS variables in `index.css`.
2. Run app in light + dark.

## Typography & layout exceptions

- **Body default** — `text-base`; labels often `text-sm`, captions `text-xs`.
- **Font** — `font-sans` / theme `--font-sans`; no ad-hoc `font-['Inter']` unless in theme.
- **Arbitrary OK rarely** — layout math (`max-h-[calc(100dvh-…)]`), third-party embeds, one-off animation durations aligned with `interaction-polish.mdc`. Never for colors or type scale.

## Checklist

- [ ] No arbitrary `text-[…]`, `bg-[…]`, raw palette classes for UI surfaces.
- [ ] shadcn primitives before custom controls; semantic tokens on composed UI.
- [ ] New status/brand colors are CSS variables in `index.css`.
- [ ] `ThemeProvider` with `attribute="class"` when dark tokens exist; user toggle when shipping dark mode.
- [ ] Light + dark smoke-tested on changed UI.
